sentences: Arvin Charles Garrison (August 17, 1922 – July 30, 1960) was an American jazz guitarist.
He led his own band at a hotel in Albany, New York, in 1941.
In 1946, Garrison recorded sessions with Charlie Parker and Dizzy Gillespie in Los Angeles, sharing the studio with Miles Davis, Dodo Marmarosa, and Lucky Thompson.
In the 1950s he returned to Toledo and played locally.
In 1960, while he was swimming, he died when he had an epileptic seizure in the water.
